      "dependencies": [1],
      "description": "Restore Ollama chat round-trip, fix live log tab, add 3-LLM selector (Ollama server, Ollama local, Gemini) to web UI.",
      "details": "Root causes fixed: (1) &msg.data[..50] panic in web_server forwarder killed the bus→WS bridge on short log messages — fixed with .min(). (2) CPU routed user_input to bus channel 'ollama_lan' but main.rs subscribed to 'ollama' — message dropped silently. Fixed by routing directly from web_server to 'ollama_{name}' per backend, bypassing CPU for chat. (3) handle_ollama_message passed the full JSON blob as the Ollama prompt instead of extracting the 'prompt' field — now extracts it. (4) Config struct in web_server had ollama: OllamaConfig (singular) but config.toml uses [[ollama]] array — struct updated. (5) CPU route_llm_request used 'ollama_lan'/'ollama_local' hardcoded strings — updated to 'ollama_server'/'ollama_local3090'. (6) Gemini handler was sync with no bus integration — fully rewritten async with timeout/retry/backoff. (7) main.rs now spawns one handler per [[ollama]] backend each on its own 'ollama_{name}' bus channel plus a dedicated 'gemini' channel handler. (8) Added dotenvy to auto-load .env (GEMINI_API_KEY). UI redesigned dark-theme with dynamic LLM pill-buttons, log timestamps, clear button, WS reconnect status dot.",
      "id": 57,
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "done",
      "subtasks": [
