    {
      "dependencies": [58],
      "description": "Preload the configured Ollama model at bot startup and send periodic keep-alive requests to prevent Ollama from unloading the model from memory between requests.",
      "details": "Implement two complementary mechanisms to ensure the Ollama model stays resident in GPU/CPU memory:\n\n1. **Startup Preload**: On bot init, send a dummy generate request (empty prompt, num_predict=0) to Ollama so the model is loaded before the first user message arrives. This eliminates the cold-start delay on the first query.\n\n2. **Keep-Alive Heartbeat**: Spawn a background Tokio task that fires a keep-alive request (POST /api/generate with `keep_alive` field set to a long duration, e.g. '1h') on a configurable interval (default: 4 minutes, just under Ollama's default 5-minute unload timeout). This prevents Ollama from evicting the model between user sessions.\n\n3. **Configuration**: Read `OLLAMA_KEEP_ALIVE_SECS` and `OLLAMA_PRELOAD` (bool) from `.env` / config so the feature can be toggled without recompiling.\n\n4. **Network resilience**: All HTTP calls must use `tokio::time::timeout`, exponential-backoff retry (up to 3 attempts), and log warnings on failure without crashing the bot — consistent with the Starlink-aware networking policy.\n\n5. **Ollama API**: Use the existing `reqwest` client. For preload send `POST /api/generate` with `{ \"model\": \"<model>\", \"prompt\": \"\", \"stream\": false }`. For keep-alive send `POST /api/generate` with `{ \"model\": \"<model>\", \"prompt\": \"\", \"keep_alive\": \"1h\", \"stream\": false }`.\n\n6. Place the preload call in `ollama/mod.rs` (or a new `ollama/keepalive.rs`) and spawn the heartbeat task from `main.rs` after the bus and Ollama client are initialised.",
      "id": 59,
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "done",
      "subtasks": [
        {
          "id": "59.1",
          "status": "done",
          "title": "Add OLLAMA_PRELOAD and OLLAMA_KEEP_ALIVE_SECS to .env and config loading",
        },
        {
          "id": "59.2",
          "status": "done",
          "title": "Implement preload_model() async fn in ollama/mod.rs with timeout + retry logic",
        },
        {
          "id": "59.3",
          "status": "done",
          "title": "Call preload_model() from main.rs after Ollama client init, guarded by OLLAMA_PRELOAD flag",
        },
        {
          "id": "59.4",
          "status": "done",
          "title": "Implement spawn_keepalive_task() that loops on interval and sends keep_alive requests",
        },
        {
          "id": "59.5",
          "status": "done",
          "title": "Spawn keepalive task from main.rs and log startup confirmation",
        },
        {
          "id": "59.6",
          "status": "done",
          "title": "Add unit tests for retry/timeout behaviour using a mock HTTP server",
        },
        {
          "id": "59.7",
          "status": "done",
          "title": "Add Error checking",
        },
        {
          "id": "59.8",
          "status": "done",
          "title": "Do Documentation .. readme , change log , data flow map , ....",
        },
      ],
      "testStrategy": "1. Start the bot and check logs for 'Ollama model preloaded successfully' before first user message.\n2. Run `ollama ps` immediately after bot start — the model should appear as loaded.\n3. Wait 5+ minutes without sending a message, then run `ollama ps` again — model should still be listed (heartbeat kept it alive).\n4. Set `OLLAMA_PRELOAD=false` in .env and verify no preload request is sent at startup.\n5. Simulate network drop (disable adapter briefly) — verify bot logs a warning and retries, does not panic.\n6. `cargo test` — all existing tests still pass.",
      "title": "Ollama Model Preload and Keep-Alive",
    },
